      Imagine Dragons
      Daniel Coulter Reynolds is best known for being the lead singer and frontman of the Grammy award-winning band, Imagine Dragons. Dan Reynolds was born on July 14, 1987. He is the seventh of nine children. He went to school at Brigham Young University but decided he wanted to pursue music as a career.

      Description

      Daniel Coulter Reynolds is an American singer and songwriter. He is the lead vocalist of the pop rock band Imagine Dragons. Reynolds also released an EP in 2011, titled Egyptian EP, as a duo with his former wife Aja Volkman under the moniker Egyptian. Wikipedia
      Born: July 14, 1987 (age 35 years), Las Vegas, Nevada, United States
      Spouse: Aja Volkman (m. 20112022)
      Children: Coco Rae Reynolds, Arrow Eve Reynolds, Gia James Reynolds, Valentine Reynolds
      Siblings: Mac Reynolds, Sarah Bleazard, Paul Quayle Reynolds, Robert Reynolds
      Height: 1.93 m
      Parents: Ronald Reynolds, Christene M. Reynolds
